Dollars 1.27, against Dollars 217.5m, or Dollars 1.22 a year earlier.
Operating revenue slipped to Dollars 2.27bn from Dollars 2.29bn.
The company said it texpected growth for the year to exceed that of 1991,
but did not expect to 'get all the way to Dun &amp; Bradstreet's long-term
goals'. It also expects second-half earnings per share to be stronger than
in the first half in spite of the uncertain worldwide economic outlook.
