second-quarter sales rise 12 per cent to Dollars 1.04bn.
Consumer healthcare sales advanced 7 per cent to Dollars 314.8m, while
medical supplies and diagnostic products recorded sales of Dollars 195.9m,
up 2 per cent in the quarter.
