<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUL 92 / Business people in Scotland more confident
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BUSINESS people in several sectors in Scotland are becoming slightly more
confident about their prospects and there are signs of a modest rise in
demand.
This is shown in the latest quarterly Scottish business survey conducted by
chambers of commerce and analysed by the Fraser of Allander Institute of
Strathclyde University, Glasgow.
The survey disclosed a slight increase in business optimism in manufacturing
and an appreciable rise in confidence in the retailing sector. The tourism
and leisure industries also reported improved confidence.
There was a sharp fall in optimism about prospects in the construction
industry compared both with three months ago and a year ago. There was no
evidence of a general upturn in demand for labour.
