revealed in detail to Beijing - a move seen to ease China's concerns about
the robustness of the colony's finances. It said Hong Kong's foreign
reserves were USDollars 29bn at the end of 1991, 12th largest in the world.
China's reserves are put at Dollars 43.6bn. The government said knowledge of
the figure would help lenders to its infrastructure programmes realistically
to assess the colony's financial health.
