FT  15 JUL 92 / Commodities and Agriculture: Bulgaria to close dozens of
unprofitable copper, zinc and lead mines
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SOFIA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Bulgaria is to close dozens of unprofitable copper, zinc and lead mines over
the next few years, sharply reducing output of the metals, reports Reuter
from Sofia.
'The zinc, lead and copper mines, or parts of them, will be closed by stages
within three years,' said Mr Politimi Paunova, a senior industry ministry
official.
The industry ministry said that in recent years annual production of copper
concentrate in Bulgaria had averaged 150,000 tonnes, lead concentrate 80,000
tonnes and zinc concentrate 70,000 tonnes. However figures were much lower
last year.
The closures are likely to result in output of copper falling to 50,000
tonnes a year, lead to 30,000 tonnes and zinc to 25,000 tonnes, a mining
industry official said.
