losses to EC taxpayers - estimated at Pounds 2.5bn a year - from the
community's complex system of grants and subsidies.
Mr Tomlinson yesterday described the EC's farm policy as 'the greatest
incentive to crime in Europe today'.
Earlier, Mr Gummer played down the extent of the problem, insisting that
frauds highlighted by the EC's court of auditors had already been tackled.
