year.
The financial services operation, Westinghouse Credit Corporation, which is
being sharply reduced after making some disastrous property investments,
reported net income of Dollars 2.1m on revenues of Dollars 172.2m, compared
with profits of Dollars 19.5m on revenues of Dollars 264m in the same period
of last year.
Westinghouse Electric's operating profit for the period was flat at Dollars
252m, with an operating profit margin of 8 per cent, against 7.9 per cent a
year ago.
Interest expense, excluding financial services operations, rose from Dollars
57m to Dollars 67m due to expenses from a new revolving credit facility,
part of Westinghouse's bolstering of its financial position following the
property problems.
Westinghouse said its broadcasting unit produced higher operating profits on
flat revenues, due to cost reductions, while electronic systems produced
flat revenues on lower operating profits due to an unfavourable sales mix.
Environmental revenues and operating profits were down; the industries
segment produced an increase in operating profit on revenues slightly
higher; and power systems saw a dip in operating profit.
