FT  15 JUL 92 / Corps may build Cambodia roads
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
JAPAN, preparing the way for its first overseas troop deployment since the
second world war, may send an engineering corps to Cambodia to build and
repair roads and bridges, Mr Sohei Miyashita, the defence minister, said
yesterday, Reuter reports from Tokyo.
The Japanese mission to serve in the United Nations peace-keeping operation
in Cambodia was expected to comprise an engineering corps and a corps to
assist helicopter transport of ceasefire monitoring missions, Mr Miyashita
said. Japan's parliament passed a law on June 15 allowing it to send up to
2,000 troops overseas to serve in UN peace-keeping missions.
