Ralphs Supermarkets, one of the largest supermarket operators in California
with 156 stores, yesterday withdrew a proposed offering of 6.075m shares,
writes Nikki Tait in New York. Ralphs is the latest in a line of companies
which have either cancelled or scaled down share offerings recently. The
food retailer said that the equity market was 'dramatically different' from
when it started the process.
