FT  15 JUL 92 / UK Company News: Prism returns record Pounds 975,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Prism Leisure Corporation, the music and computer games group traded on the
USM, returned record profits of Pounds 975,000 pre-tax for the 52 weeks
ended March 29.
The 28 per cent improvement over the previous year's Pounds 761,000 was
achieved on the back of an 8 per cent rise in turnover to Pounds 13.5m.
Earnings rose by 5p to 16.8p and an increased final dividend of 3.95p makes
a 5.45p (4.95p) total. Year-end cash balances totalled Pounds 800,000.
