FT  15 JUL 92 / UK Company News: Enlarged Pelican improves to Pounds 0.45m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Pelican Group, a USM-quoted restaurant operator, reported pre-tax
profits of Pounds 453,000 for the year to March 31, against Pounds 446,000
which included Pounds 168,000 of property profits.
Turnover improved from Pounds 4.72m to Pounds 6.32m. During the period the
expansion programme continued and the group now has 17 restaurants and has
recently acquired two further sites.
Earnings per share fell from 7.5p to 3p reflecting last year's rights issue
and shares issued for an acquisition in January 1991. The company is
proposing to maintain its single dividend at 1p.
An extraordinary charge of Pounds 204,000 (Pounds 92,000), mainly relating
to the costs of the rights issue, left retained profits for the year down at
Pounds 56,000 (Pounds 258,000).
